.nf
Radio Shack ROMs, PALs and System disks for Model III/4/4D/4P systems

.fi
These ROMs, PALs and diskettes were obtained from Radio Shack when they
reduced their Model 4, 4D and 4P parts inventory.  We carry them for
people who desire to make their own repairs or upgrades.  

NOTE: Unless otherwise stated, documentation is not provided with these
replacement parts.
.br

ATTENTION:   We no longer purchase Radio Shack ROM and PALs.
We will continue to carry these parts until our supply is
exhausted.
.nf


Universal Character Generator - used in all Model 4/4D/4P systems	
										Specify 4GRCG00	$6.00

.fi
If your Model 4 was built before 1984, it may contain an obsolete
character generator.  About that time, Radio Shack switched to a "universal"
character generator which was used in all subsequent U.S. and international
versions of the Model 4, 4P, 4D and 2000.  To check to see if you have the
older part, go into Model 4 Disk BASIC and type:
.br
	?CHR$(0);CHR$(26) <ENTER>
.br
If a vertical line is displayed, then you have the newer part.  If you see the
letter 'a' or some other character, you should consider upgrading your
machine.  Instructions for installation of this genuine Radio Shack part
are included.  Documentation on the universal character set begins on page A-58 of the
TRSDOS 6.2 Disk System Owners Manual.
.br


.nf
